# Bangazon API

----
## Usage
1. ```git clone git@github.com:NSS-Alleged-Donkeys/BangazonAPI.git```
1. Open SQL Server Management Studio and run BangazonAPI.sql to build and seed database
1. Launch Visual Studio
1. In ```appsettings.json``` change the default connection string to your local machine from SSMS
1. Run program from Visual Studio
1. Launch Postman

1. Test `GET, PUT, POST, DELETE` for 
http://localhost:5000/api/customer
http://localhost:5000/api/computer
http://localhost:5000/api/department
http://localhost:5000/api/employee
http://localhost:5000/api/paymentType
http://localhost:5000/api/product
http://localhost:5000/api/productType
http://localhost:5000/api/trainingProgram


